You could save the future in the Future implementation<p><pre><code>    type future struct {
        completed   bool
        result      interface{}
        ch        <-chan interface{}
    }
</code></pre>
Edit: Or just check if the channel is closed<p><pre><code>    func (f *future) Wait() interface{} {
        v, ok := <- ch
        if ok { f.result = v; return v }
        else  { return f.result }
    }</code></pre>
